044/**
045 * Utility classes and methods for the {@link Rest @Rest} annotation.
046 *
047 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
048 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/RestAnnotatedClassBasics">@Rest-Annotated Class Basics</a>
049 * </ul>
050 */
051public class RestAnnotation {
052
053   //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
054   // Static
055   //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
056
057   /** Default value */
058   public static final Rest DEFAULT = create().build();
059
060   /**
061    * Instantiates a new builder for this class.
062    *
063    * @return A new builder object.
064    */
065   public static Builder create() {
066      return new Builder();
067   }
068
069   /**
070    * Instantiates a new builder for this class.
071    *
072    * @param on The targets this annotation applies to.
073    * @return A new builder object.
074    */
075   public static Builder create(Class<?>...on) {
076      return create().on(on);
077   }
078
079   /**
080    * Instantiates a new builder for this class.
081    *
082    * @param on The targets this annotation applies to.
083    * @return A new builder object.
084    */
085   public static Builder create(String...on) {
086      return create().on(on);
087   }

661   private static class Impl extends TargetedAnnotationTImpl implements Rest {
662
663      private final Class<? extends Encoder>[] encoders;
664      private final Class<? extends HttpPartParser> partParser;
665      private final Class<? extends HttpPartSerializer> partSerializer;
666      private final Class<? extends StaticFiles> staticFiles;
667      private final Class<? extends ResponseProcessor>[] responseProcessors;
668      private final Class<? extends CallLogger> callLogger;
669      private final Class<? extends RestConverter>[] converters;
670      private final Class<? extends RestGuard>[] guards;
671      private final Class<? extends SwaggerProvider> swaggerProvider;
672      private final Class<? extends RestOpArg>[] restOpArgs;
673      private final Class<? extends BeanStore> beanStore;
674      private final Class<? extends RestChildren> restChildrenClass;
675      private final Class<? extends RestOperations> restOperationsClass;
676      private final Class<? extends DebugEnablement> debugEnablement;
677      private final Class<? extends Serializer>[] serializers;
678      private final Class<?>[] children, parsers;
679      private final Swagger swagger;
680      private final String disableContentParam, allowedHeaderParams, allowedMethodHeaders, allowedMethodParams, clientVersionHeader, config, debug, debugOn, defaultAccept, defaultCharset, defaultContentType, maxInput, messages, path, renderResponseStackTraces, roleGuard, rolesDeclared, siteName, uriAuthority, uriContext, uriRelativity, uriResolution;
681      private final String[] consumes, produces, defaultRequestAttributes, defaultRequestHeaders, defaultResponserHeaders, title;
682
683      Impl(Builder b) {
684         super(b);
685         this.disableContentParam = b.disableContentParam;
686         this.allowedHeaderParams = b.allowedHeaderParams;
687         this.allowedMethodHeaders = b.allowedMethodHeaders;
688         this.allowedMethodParams = b.allowedMethodParams;
689         this.beanStore = b.beanStore;
690         this.callLogger = b.callLogger;
691         this.children = copyOf(b.children);
692         this.clientVersionHeader = b.clientVersionHeader;
693         this.config = b.config;
694         this.consumes = copyOf(b.consumes);
695         this.converters = copyOf(b.converters);
696         this.debug = b.debug;
697         this.debugEnablement = b.debugEnablement;
698         this.debugOn = b.debugOn;
699         this.defaultAccept = b.defaultAccept;
700         this.defaultCharset = b.defaultCharset;
701         this.defaultContentType = b.defaultContentType;
702         this.defaultRequestAttributes = copyOf(b.defaultRequestAttributes);
703         this.defaultRequestHeaders = copyOf(b.defaultRequestHeaders);
704         this.defaultResponserHeaders = copyOf(b.defaultResponseHeaders);
705         this.encoders = copyOf(b.encoders);
706         this.guards = copyOf(b.guards);
707         this.maxInput = b.maxInput;
708         this.messages = b.messages;
709         this.parsers = copyOf(b.parsers);
710         this.partParser = b.partParser;
711         this.partSerializer = b.partSerializer;
712         this.path = b.path;
713         this.produces = copyOf(b.produces);
714         this.renderResponseStackTraces = b.renderResponseStackTraces;
715         this.responseProcessors = copyOf(b.responseProcessors);
716         this.restChildrenClass = b.restChildrenClass;
717         this.restOperationsClass = b.restOperationsClass;
718         this.restOpArgs = copyOf(b.restOpArgs);
719         this.roleGuard = b.roleGuard;
720         this.rolesDeclared = b.rolesDeclared;
721         this.serializers = copyOf(b.serializers);
722         this.siteName = b.siteName;
723         this.staticFiles = b.staticFiles;
724         this.swagger = b.swagger;
725         this.swaggerProvider = b.swaggerProvider;
726         this.title = copyOf(b.title);
727         this.uriAuthority = b.uriAuthority;
728         this.uriContext = b.uriContext;
729         this.uriRelativity = b.uriRelativity;
730         this.uriResolution = b.uriResolution;
731         postConstruct();
732      }

969   /**
970    * Applies {@link Rest} annotations to a {@link org.apache.juneau.rest.RestContext.Builder}.
971    */
972   public static class RestContextApply extends AnnotationApplier<Rest,RestContext.Builder> {
973
974      /**
975       * Constructor.
976       *
977       * @param vr The resolver for resolving values in annotations.
978       */
979      public RestContextApply(VarResolverSession vr) {
980         super(Rest.class, RestContext.Builder.class, vr);
981      }
982
983      @Override
984      public void apply(AnnotationInfo<Rest> ai, RestContext.Builder b) {
985         Rest a = ai.inner();
986
987         classes(a.serializers()).ifPresent(x -> b.serializers().add(x));
988         classes(a.parsers()).ifPresent(x -> b.parsers().add(x));
989         type(a.partSerializer()).ifPresent(x -> b.partSerializer().type(x));
990         type(a.partParser()).ifPresent(x -> b.partParser().type(x));
991         stream(a.produces()).map(MediaType::of).forEach(x -> b.produces(x));
992         stream(a.consumes()).map(MediaType::of).forEach(x -> b.consumes(x));
993         stream(a.defaultRequestAttributes()).map(BasicNamedAttribute::ofPair).forEach(x -> b.defaultRequestAttributes(x));
994         stream(a.defaultRequestHeaders()).map(HttpHeaders::stringHeader).forEach(x -> b.defaultRequestHeaders(x));
995         stream(a.defaultResponseHeaders()).map(HttpHeaders::stringHeader).forEach(x -> b.defaultResponseHeaders(x));
996         string(a.defaultAccept()).map(HttpHeaders::accept).ifPresent(x -> b.defaultRequestHeaders(x));
997         string(a.defaultContentType()).map(HttpHeaders::contentType).ifPresent(x -> b.defaultRequestHeaders(x));
998         b.responseProcessors().add(a.responseProcessors());
999         b.children((Object[])a.children());
1000         b.restOpArgs(a.restOpArgs());
1001         classes(a.encoders()).ifPresent(x -> b.encoders().add(x));
1002         string(a.uriContext()).ifPresent(x -> b.uriContext(x));
1003         string(a.uriAuthority()).ifPresent(x -> b.uriAuthority(x));
1004         string(a.uriRelativity()).map(UriRelativity::valueOf).ifPresent(x -> b.uriRelativity(x));
1005         string(a.uriResolution()).map(UriResolution::valueOf).ifPresent(x -> b.uriResolution(x));
1006         b.messages().location(string(a.messages()).orElse(null));
1007         type(a.staticFiles()).ifPresent(x -> b.staticFiles().type(x));
1008         string(a.path()).ifPresent(x -> b.path(x));
1009         string(a.clientVersionHeader()).ifPresent(x -> b.clientVersionHeader(x));
1010         type(a.callLogger()).ifPresent(x -> b.callLogger().type(x));
1011         type(a.swaggerProvider()).ifPresent(x -> b.swaggerProvider(x));
1012         type(a.restChildrenClass()).ifPresent(x -> b.restChildrenClass(x));
1013         type(a.restOperationsClass()).ifPresent(x -> b.restOperationsClass(x));
1014         type(a.debugEnablement()).ifPresent(x -> b.debugEnablement().type(x));
1015         string(a.disableContentParam()).map(Boolean::parseBoolean).ifPresent(x -> b.disableContentParam(x));
1016         string(a.allowedHeaderParams()).ifPresent(x -> b.allowedHeaderParams(x));
1017         string(a.allowedMethodHeaders()).ifPresent(x -> b.allowedMethodHeaders(x));
1018         string(a.allowedMethodParams()).ifPresent(x -> b.allowedMethodParams(x));
1019         bool(a.renderResponseStackTraces()).ifPresent(x -> b.renderResponseStackTraces(x));
1020      }
1021   }
1022
1023   /**
1024    * Applies {@link Rest} annotations to a {@link org.apache.juneau.rest.RestOpContext.Builder}.
1025    */
1026   public static class RestOpContextApply extends AnnotationApplier<Rest,RestOpContext.Builder> {
1027
1028      /**
1029       * Constructor.
1030       *
1031       * @param vr The resolver for resolving values in annotations.
1032       */
1033      public RestOpContextApply(VarResolverSession vr) {
1034         super(Rest.class, RestOpContext.Builder.class, vr);
1035      }
1036
1037      @Override
1038      public void apply(AnnotationInfo<Rest> ai, RestOpContext.Builder b) {
1039         Rest a = ai.inner();
1040
1041         stream(a.produces()).map(MediaType::of).forEach(x -> b.produces(x));
1042         stream(a.consumes()).map(MediaType::of).forEach(x -> b.consumes(x));
1043         b.converters().append(a.converters());
1044         b.guards().append(a.guards());
1045         string(a.defaultCharset()).map(Charset::forName).ifPresent(x -> b.defaultCharset(x));
1046         string(a.maxInput()).ifPresent(x -> b.maxInput(x));
1047         cdl(a.rolesDeclared()).forEach(x -> b.rolesDeclared(x));
1048         string(a.roleGuard()).ifPresent(x -> b.roleGuard(x));
1049      }
1050   }
